Freescale's Yocto Project BSP
=============================

To get the BSP you need to have `repo` installed and use it as:

Install the `repo` utility:

$: mkdir ~/bin
$: curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo  > ~/bin/repo
$: chmod a+x ~/bin/repo
$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin

Download the BSP source:

$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin
$: mkdir fsl-yocto-bsp
$: cd fsl-yocto-bsp
$: repo init -u http://sw-stash.freescale.net/scm/yocto/fsl-yocto-repo.git -b fido_freescale_qoriq_sdk_v1.9
$: repo sync
$: MACHINE=<board> . ./fsl-setup-env <build-dir>

